00:00:05,454 --> 00:00:11,516
I'm Heli Salomaa. I'm a costume designer, and I'm here to talk about how I was integrated

2
00:00:11,616 --> 00:00:17,698
into the character pipeline of Remedy Entertainment's Control. Before I start, remember to turn

3
00:00:17,738 --> 00:00:23,280
off your noisemakers and remember to fill out the evaluation form after the session.

4
00:00:28,161 --> 00:00:30,102
Control is Chessie Faden's story.

5
00:00:31,584 --> 00:00:35,126
It takes place in the headquarters of the Federal Bureau of Control,

6
00:00:35,507 --> 00:00:40,230
where Jessie uncovers the answers she seeks as she grows into the role of the director.

7
00:00:41,491 --> 00:00:45,594
Remedy is known for narrative-driven cinematic single-player action games

8
00:00:45,815 --> 00:00:51,439
that have a strong lead character. This presentation is based on my work as a

9
00:00:51,479 --> 00:00:54,701
costume artist on Control, which will be released this year.

10
00:00:56,768 --> 00:00:59,449
Before Kontroll, I had worked on costumes for live arts,

11
00:00:59,689 --> 00:01:01,750
such as dance, circus, and theater,

12
00:01:02,410 --> 00:01:05,271
and digital costumes in animation and VR.

13
00:01:06,691 --> 00:01:09,712
In 2016, I wanted to write my master's thesis

14
00:01:09,772 --> 00:01:10,933
about costumes in games,

15
00:01:11,413 --> 00:01:13,514
and asked Remini if I could come work for them

16
00:01:13,694 --> 00:01:15,114
to see how they do things,

17
00:01:15,414 --> 00:01:18,235
and if I would be of any help in the character process.

18
00:01:19,895 --> 00:01:22,796
I ended up working on the costumes of Kontroll for two years

19
00:01:23,056 --> 00:01:25,397
and wrote the thesis about this collaboration.

20
00:01:27,484 --> 00:01:32,386
The main finding in the thesis was that the people who design characters' appearance for games

21
00:01:33,067 --> 00:01:36,748
and the people who design costumes for live arts have the same job.

22
00:01:38,269 --> 00:01:43,291
Both professions create characters from the inside of the story and concentrate on expressing

23
00:01:43,611 --> 00:01:50,474
the character's age, background, social status, and the time period, environment, and climate through appearance.

24
00:01:53,676 --> 00:01:55,837
Costume is often confused with fashion.

25
00:01:57,788 --> 00:02:03,594
Fashion designers design clothes for the general public and concentrate on the aesthetics features of clothing.

26
00:02:06,036 --> 00:02:11,061
Costume design is character specific and concentrates on the narrative features of clothing.

27
00:02:12,395 --> 00:02:15,297
It includes not only what the character is wearing and why,

28
00:02:15,857 --> 00:02:17,919
but also how the garment is worn

29
00:02:18,099 --> 00:02:21,462
and how the character's previous actions, events in the story

30
00:02:21,642 --> 00:02:26,025
or passing time have affected the quality and condition of the clothing.

31
00:02:27,006 --> 00:02:30,309
Costume designers also define how the characters have their hair

32
00:02:30,769 --> 00:02:34,672
and if they have physical characteristics, such as tattoos or scars.

33
00:02:36,654 --> 00:02:40,177
This job description also applies to realistic character design.

34
00:02:42,392 --> 00:02:44,333
Despite the form of the visual narrative,

35
00:02:44,573 --> 00:02:47,913
the characters' appearance communicate information about the world

36
00:02:48,013 --> 00:02:49,393
where the narrative takes place.

37
00:02:50,574 --> 00:02:54,654
The main difference in designing the costumes for games or live arts is

38
00:02:55,235 --> 00:02:58,755
that the costume design is mostly connected to the physical human body.

39
00:03:00,435 --> 00:03:02,756
In live arts, the restrictions of costume design

40
00:03:02,896 --> 00:03:05,176
are connected to the reality and physical laws,

41
00:03:05,696 --> 00:03:09,397
while costume in games is restricted by the technology.

42
00:03:13,287 --> 00:03:17,589
The thesis and this presentation concentrate on games that are based on human characters

43
00:03:17,749 --> 00:03:21,450
and are either realistic or represent stylized realism,

44
00:03:22,110 --> 00:03:26,271
since most of my work on Control was about adding realism through the costumes.

45
00:03:27,412 --> 00:03:31,753
This talk refers to my experience in making games that remedy as a costume artist,

46
00:03:32,213 --> 00:03:36,055
and the utilized methods are considered through the character pipeline of Remedy

47
00:03:36,455 --> 00:03:39,696
and apply primarily on the Remedy's character process.

48
00:03:43,105 --> 00:03:54,148
During this session, I'll talk about how learning the similarities and differences of the costume production between game and film industry helped me to integrate into the process, the character process.

49
00:03:56,109 --> 00:04:00,050
I will also introduce three examples of costume work on Control.

50
