00:10:16,236 --> 00:10:19,197
In order to design the protagonist and the rest of the characters,

111
00:10:19,257 --> 00:10:21,678
we need to be familiar with the setting of the game

112
00:10:22,338 --> 00:10:24,579
and the environment the characters will be seen in.

113
00:10:25,819 --> 00:10:29,501
The story of Control takes place in the oldest house,

114
00:10:29,681 --> 00:10:32,642
which is the headquarters of the Federal Bureau of Control.

115
00:10:33,342 --> 00:10:35,423
The oldest house is located in New York

116
00:10:35,663 --> 00:10:38,704
and it's built in the brutalistic architectural style.

117
00:10:47,355 --> 00:10:57,500
August 4th, 1964. Bureau agents discover the oldest house, investigating an altered world event case in the New York City subway tunnels.

118
00:10:58,420 --> 00:11:05,523
It's a place of power. From the outside, it looks like an ordinary building. A brutalist skyscraper.

119
00:11:07,464 --> 00:11:12,806
But inside, it breaks the laws of our reality. Unstable. Mad. Shifting.

120
00:11:16,280 --> 00:11:19,642
There are rooms in the building where other dimensions leak in.

121
00:11:20,262 --> 00:11:22,723
We call these rooms thresholds.

122
00:11:26,765 --> 00:11:30,006
There is a connection between our minds and the unknown,

123
00:11:30,526 --> 00:11:33,547
often hostile forces intruding on our world.

124
00:11:36,208 --> 00:11:40,590
These forces gravitate toward everyday objects, a gun, a television,

125
00:11:41,110 --> 00:11:43,931
a house with a reputation of being haunted.

126
00:11:46,948 --> 00:11:50,270
So somehow, we affect these events.

127
00:11:51,230 --> 00:11:53,551
We're holding the key, but we don't have a clue

128
00:11:53,692 --> 00:11:54,732
on how to use it.

129
00:11:57,193 --> 00:12:00,715
We're dealing with dangerous, unknown forces here.

130
00:12:02,616 --> 00:12:04,617
What's the cause and what's the effect?

131
00:12:05,397 --> 00:12:06,457
Are we the starting point,

132
00:12:07,138 --> 00:12:09,079
or just the necessary evil in this?

133
00:12:10,819 --> 00:12:13,641
We're on a mission to find answers to these questions.

134
00:12:17,097 --> 00:12:27,161
die trying. This is Zachariah Trench, the Director of the Federal Bureau of Control.

135
00:12:38,125 --> 00:12:43,767
As mentioned in the trailer, the environment is an ever-shifting supernatural location that

136
00:12:43,887 --> 00:12:46,228
exists outside of the laws of reality.

137
00:12:47,338 --> 00:12:51,001
The FPC has created a combination of science and ritualism

138
00:12:51,381 --> 00:12:54,584
in order to stabilise some of the oldest house topography.

139
00:12:56,506 --> 00:12:58,788
The equipment of Breaux is old-fashioned.

140
00:12:59,408 --> 00:13:03,932
The supernatural environment demands tested and confirmed equipment

141
00:13:04,092 --> 00:13:06,034
that is more stable than the modern ones.

142
00:13:06,815 --> 00:13:13,300
Changing the gear might risk the stability of the unpredictable environment.

143
00:13:15,869 --> 00:13:23,260
In addition to studying supernatural elements that they actively seek out, contain, study and attempt to control within this interior,

144
00:13:23,961 --> 00:13:31,712
FBC also researches various forms of protection from supernatural phenomena to shield the employees.

145
00:13:35,249 --> 00:13:39,273
The people who work in this environment, the employees of FPC,

146
00:13:39,953 --> 00:13:44,257
are regular bureau staff such as office workers, maintenance and security.

147
00:13:45,338 --> 00:13:50,062
I created the bureau's dress code to frame the style of these NPCs in the game.

148
00:13:50,943 --> 00:13:57,428
I kept the style classic, timeless and generic to contrast to the unpredictable supernatural environment.

149
00:13:59,764 --> 00:14:03,306
As the equipment of brawl, also the office dress code is old-fashioned

150
00:14:03,687 --> 00:14:06,328
and leans back to the 60s to 80s office wear

151
00:14:06,669 --> 00:14:09,150
that was based on straight pants and collared shirts

152
00:14:09,591 --> 00:14:11,432
and at some office jobs still is.

153
00:14:12,673 --> 00:14:15,494
Most of Kontrol's costumes are based on these fundaments,

154
00:14:16,015 --> 00:14:19,057
except for maintenance and tactically demanding costumes.

155
00:14:19,857 --> 00:14:23,239
However, FPC employees always dress up appropriately

156
00:14:23,420 --> 00:14:25,401
and treat their clothes with respect.

157
00:14:27,534 --> 00:14:29,836
Here are a couple of NPC characters I made.

158
00:14:30,977 --> 00:14:35,781
Even the laboratory worker is based on a collared shirt and straight pants.

159
00:14:36,942 --> 00:14:39,804
You might notice quality differences between these concepts.

160
00:14:40,585 --> 00:14:43,907
During the years in live arts I always drew everything by hand,

161
00:14:44,027 --> 00:14:47,290
but when I started at Remedy I had to learn how to use Photoshop.

162
00:14:48,211 --> 00:14:50,052
The lab guy is one of my earliest concepts.

163
00:14:53,822 --> 00:14:57,865
And we get to the first example, developing the protagonist.

164
00:15:03,109 --> 00:15:06,492
After I was familiar with the environment the characters will inhabit

165
00:15:06,772 --> 00:15:10,395
and created the dress code to define the base style of NPC's look,

166
00:15:10,975 --> 00:15:14,558
I created a reference board to explore Jessie's style.

167
00:15:16,513 --> 00:15:22,554
The main idea here was to communicate Jessie's externality to brouhaha through style and materials.

168
00:15:23,354 --> 00:15:28,716
Jessie wears contemporary relatable street clothes and her materials are denim and jersey.

169
00:15:29,436 --> 00:15:31,476
She wears the only jeans in the building.

170
00:15:32,457 --> 00:15:39,598
In contrast, brouhaha clothes are made of durable and high quality materials and their style is old fashioned and well fitted.

171
00:15:40,698 --> 00:15:41,939
Jessie's not into fashion.

172
00:15:42,559 --> 00:15:45,820
What matters for her more is the functionality of the clothing.

173
00:15:47,282 --> 00:15:50,845
When Jessie arrives at Breaux, she rebels against the dress code.

174
00:15:51,345 --> 00:15:54,947
Whatever she is given to wear, she rolls up sleeves if possible,

175
00:15:55,087 --> 00:15:59,490
or keeps items of her own outfit, such as her jersey shirt or shoes.

176
00:16:00,231 --> 00:16:05,014
Her growth into the role of the director is also expressed through her appearance.

177
00:16:08,727 --> 00:16:15,112
During the pre-production of Control, I made around 130 costume variations of Jesse's outfit.

178
00:16:16,233 --> 00:16:22,097
Jesse's character was developed alongside the narrative, and during the process of defining our protagonist,

179
00:16:22,517 --> 00:16:26,901
the style went from official style to street style, then a bit over the top to punk,

180
00:16:27,581 --> 00:16:31,764
then to a soft casual look, before Jesse's current style started forming up.

181
00:16:32,968 --> 00:16:38,218
Actually the reference board of the previous slide was not the first but probably the fifth of a kind

182
00:16:38,999 --> 00:16:43,347
and here it applies to the last two rows of costume variations.

183
00:16:46,443 --> 00:16:52,966
When I found the style that the team agreed with, I created this costume board for Jessie's life concepts.

184
00:16:53,787 --> 00:16:57,449
Based on the board, I bought actual clothes for costume fitting.

185
00:16:58,589 --> 00:17:02,531
At this point, we knew that when Courtney Hope, who acts Jessie, comes over,

186
00:17:02,931 --> 00:17:06,893
we will dress her up as Jessie and have a photoshoot with her in character.

187
00:17:09,123 --> 00:17:15,849
